u_{xx}+2u_{xy}-3u_{yy}=0
\xi=x+y
\eta=x-\frac{1}{3}y
u(x,y)=F(x+y)+G(x-\frac{1}{3}y)
u(x=0,y)=y, u_x(x=0,y)=y
F(y)+G(-\frac{1}{3}y)=y
u(x,y)=F(x+y)+G(y-3x)
u(0,y)=y
F(y)+G(y)=y
u_x(0,y)=y
F'(y)-3G'(y)=y
F(y)-3G(y)=\dfrac{y^2}{2}+c
\therefore F(y)=\dfrac{y^2+6y+2c}{8},G(y)=\dfrac{y-y^2-2c}{8}
\therefore u(x,y)=\dfrac{(x+y)^2+6(x+y)+y-3x-(y-3x)^2}{8}
